(Using the less-than-or-equal comparison operator on null)

Nada is nothing

Say "null isn't less than or equal to mysterious"
Mystery is mysterious
say Mystery is as little as Nada
say Mystery is as little as nothing
say nothing is as little as Mystery
say nothing is as little as mysterious

Say "null is less than or equal to itself"
say Nada is as low as Nada
say Nada is as low as nothing
say nobody is as low as Nada
say nowhere is as low as empty

Say "null isn't less than or equal to booleans"
Rightness is right
Wrongness is wrong
say Nada is as small as Rightness
say Nada is as small as Wrongness
say true is as small as nothing
say false is as small as nothing

